timings.name: Additional Follow-up Sampling for TE ADA

conditions.name: Admission Rescheduling Condition
conditions.description: Condition for rescheduling admission to the CRU on Day 1.
conditions.text: Admission can be rescheduled if PG level is not 90 to 250 mg/dL on Day 1.

conditions.name: Insulin Infusion Stop Condition
conditions.description: Condition to stop the insulin infusion used to induce hypoglycemia.
conditions.text: Insulin infusion is stopped once bedside PG is <60 mg/dL.

conditions.name: Interim Safety Review Condition
conditions.description: Condition for continuing the study after an initial cohort.
conditions.text: Safety data will be reviewed after the first 6 patients are administered LY900018 in Period 2. If no clinically significant safety findings for treatment or study procedure are noted, the remaining patients will be dosed.

conditions.name: Patient Replacement Criteria
conditions.description: Criteria for replacing a discontinued patient.
conditions.text: If patients discontinue from the study before completion of both periods with evaluable primary outcome for any reason, the patient may be replaced. Replacement should not occur beyond 75 patients enrolled.

conditions.name: Non-inferiority Condition
conditions.description: Statistical criteria for declaring non-inferiority of LY900018.
conditions.text: Non-inferiority of LY900018 will be declared if the upper limit of the 2-sided 95% CI constructed on the difference in percentage (IMG - LY900018) is less than the NIM of 10%.

transitionRules.name: Transition to Additional Follow-up
transitionRules.text: Patients with TE ADA at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

transitionRules.name: Continuation of Inadvertently Enrolled Patient
transitionRules.text: If a patient who did not meet enrollment criteria was inadvertently enrolled, a discussion must occur between the Lilly CP/CRP and the investigator to determine if the patient may continue in the study with documented approval.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Completion
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Patient completes both treatment periods and the final follow-up visit.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: End of Additional Follow-up for TE ADA
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Additional follow-up for TE ADA ends when the titer returns to baseline or 1 year after the last dose of study treatment, whichever is first.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Discontinuation by Patient Decision
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The patient, or legal representative, requests to be withdrawn from the study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Discontinuation by Investigator Decision
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The investigator decides that the patient should be discontinued from the study for any reason.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Discontinuation for Other Study Enrollment
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Patient enrolls in any other clinical study involving an investigational product or other medical research judged not to be compatible with this study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Discontinuation for Medical/Safety/Regulatory Reasons
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Participation in the study needs to be stopped for medical, safety, regulatory, or other reasons.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Discontinuation for Safety
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Following the review of the safety data from the first 6 patients to complete Period 2 Day 1, the study will be stopped if deemed necessary for patient safety.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Lost to Follow-up
scheduleTimelineExits.description: A patient will be considered lost to follow-up if he or she repeatedly fails to return for scheduled visits and is unable to be contacted by the study site.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Interim Safety Review Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point to continue dosing remaining patients based on safety review of the first 6 patients completing Period 2.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Inadvertent Enrollment Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point for continuing an inadvertently enrolled patient, which requires discussion and documented approval.
